Other provinces in Western Canada WILL NOT PROHIBIT pest control products because of their Science-Based approach.
 
There Is A Real Trend AGAINST Pesticide Bans.
 
 
 
Alberta
 
 
Anti-Pesticide PROHIBITION in Alberta is NOT NECESSARY.
 
In 2011, the Government of Alberta STOPPED THE TREND TOWARDS NEEDLESS, SENSELESS, and MALICIOUS PROHIBITION.
 
On August 9th, 2011, the Government of Alberta stated that it WOULD NOT CREATE RESTRICTIONS OR LAWS THAT CONFLICT WITH THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT, that is relied upon for health and safety assessments of pest control products.
 
Consequently, the Government of Alberta indicated that is has NO INTENT TO PROHIBIT THE SALE OF ANY PEST CONTROL PRODUCT.
 
Alberta has monitored Anti-Pesticide PROHIBITIONS over the past few years and the approaches taken by other jurisdictions, and has found THE BASIS FOR ACTION CONFUSING AND INCONSISTENT.
 
There Is A Real Trend AGAINST Pesticide Bans.
 
 
