CropLife Newsletter  ―  Urban Update
 
 
Manitoba Conservation is holding an ON-LINE CONSULTATION about pest control products used in the Urban Landscape in the Province of Manitoba.
 
CropLife encourages you to have your say and support the ongoing use of pest control tools that are Health-Canada-Approved.
 
SEND AN E-MAIL TO MANITOBA CONSERVATION to let them know that YOU DO NOT SUPPORT A BAN.
 
cosmetic.pesticides@gov.mb.ca
 
STOP PROHIBITION in Manitoba to stop it NATIONALLY !
 
August 2012
 
 
 
CropLife Canada
 
 
CropLife Canada is the trade association representing manufacturers, developers and distributors of pest control products, including those designed specifically for urban use.
 
 
THE WISDOM OF HEPWORTH, LORNE  –  THE NATION'S MOST EFFECTIVE AND CONSISTENT SPOKESMAN  –  CROPLIFE CANADA ( Web-Page )
 
http://wp.me/P1jq40-2eG
 
 
 
Manitoba Conservation
 
 
Manitoba Conservation is a department of the Government of Manitoba that oversees environmental issues.
 
Manitoba Conservation is INFESTED WITH SUBVERSIVE ANTI-PESTICIDE LUNATICS.
 
Manitoba Conservation will, BEYOND ANY DOUBT, RECOMMEND ANTI-PESTICIDE PROHIBITION.
 
Nevertheless, Manitoba Conservation will MAINTAIN THE PRETENSE of listening to what the public had to say with its MOCK ON-LINE CONSULTATION.
 
 
 
Sample Letter To Manitoba Conservation
 
 
To :  
 
Manitoba Conservation
 
cosmetic.pesticides@gov.mb.ca
 
 
Subject :  
 
RESPONSE TO THE ON-LINE CONSULTATION
 
I do not support a ban on lawn and garden products.
 
These products are thoroughly assessed by Health Canada and are important tools for ensuring Manitoban’s green spaces remain vibrant and healthy. 
 
I trust Health Canada to ensure that the pesticides it approves are safe and effective, and I want to be sure that I have access to these products to protect my property from insects, weeds, and diseases. 
 
Please don’t let misinformation influence you to ban products that I consider important and that Health Canada has approved as safe.
 
 
 
Respond To Manitoba's On-Line Consultation
 
 
Anyone from the Green Space Industry who DOES NOT respond to Manitoba’s ON-LINE CONSULTATION is a PITIFUL FOOL and an IDIOT, and DOES NOT DESERVE a career, or a business, or any success in the Green Space Industry.
 
It does not matter if you do not live in Manitoba.
 
STOP THE SPREAD OF ANTI-PESTICIDE TERRORISM !
 
RESPOND TO THE ON-LINE CONSULTATION  …  SEVERAL TIMES !
 
 
 
PROHIBITION Is NOT Necessary
 
 
Anti-Pesticide Lunatics have INFESTED the Government of Manitoba which is DEMANDING ANTI-PESTICIDE PROHIBITION.
 
Manitoba is running an MOCK ON-LINE CONSULTATION DONE IN BAD FAITH under the PRETENSE of gauging citizens’ views on the PROHIBITION against pest control products used in the Urban Landscape.
 
PROHIBITION in Manitoba IS NOT NECESSARY since pest control products are HEALTH-CANADA-APPROVED, FEDERALLY-LEGAL, PRACTICALLY-NON-TOXIC, SCIENTIFICALLY-SAFE, and CAUSE NO HARM.
 
As reported through Health Canada’s VAST TOXICOLOGY DATABASE, scientific research shows that NO HARM WILL OCCUR when pest control products are used properly.
 
If/when Manitoba IMPOSES Anti-Pesticide PROHIBITION, it will have done so in DEFIANCE of Health Canada’s SCIENTIFIC ASSESSMENTS proving that pest control products are SCIENTIFICALLY-SAFE  …  ASSESSMENTS that can take up to TEN YEARS and COST HUNDREDS OF MILLIONS OF DOLLARS.
 
Health Canada’s ASSESSMENTS prove that there are NO harmful irreversible effects to health and the environment when pest control products are used properly !
 
There is NOT ONE KNOWN ILLNESS or DEATH from the proper use of pest control products used in the Urban Landscape.
 
The Government of Manitoba WILL NOT SPEND ANY MONEY on ANY SCIENTIFIC ASSESSMENT of pest control products.
 
This is because NO ONE within the Government of Manitoba has ANY recognized training, background, experience in pest control products.
 
Health Canada, and NOT Manitoba, has THE ESSENTIAL EXPERTISE on the subject of pest control products.
 
Non-Expert Anti-Pesticide Lunatics have been PERPETUATING NOTHING BUT MYTHS regarding the need for PROHIBITION in Manitoba.
 
 
